{"taskId":"BRAIN-PRIORITIZER-URGENT-TS","summary":"Enhance brain prioritizer to inject urgent remediation when tsErrors>0 (add synthetic enhancement id 0 with highest score)","files":["/workspaces/studio/scripts/brain/mission/prioritizer.ts"],"status":"done","createdAt":"2025-08-19T09:48:00.000Z","updatedAt":"2025-08-19T09:47:49.935Z","message":"Modify prioritizer.ts: If tsErrors>0, prepend synthetic enhancement with id 0 title 'Urgent: Resolve TypeScript errors' reason 'Compilation blockers impede all progress.' Score should exceed others (e.g., 100). Include tsErrors count in reason. Keep existing logic; ensure ordering ranks this first. Add doc comment clarifying urgent remediation injection."}
{"taskId":"BRAIN-PRIORITIZER-URGENT-LINT","summary":"Enhance brain prioritizer to inject urgent remediation when lintErrors>0 (synthetic id 6)","files":["/workspaces/studio/scripts/brain/mission/prioritizer.ts"],"status":"done","createdAt":"2025-08-19T09:48:00.000Z","updatedAt":"2025-08-19T09:47:55.051Z","message":"Modify prioritizer.ts: If lintErrors>0, inject synthetic enhancement id 6 title 'Resolve ESLint errors' reason 'Lint errors reduce code health and block clean CI.' Score lower than urgent TS but high (e.g., 80). Only include when lintErrors>0. Keep deterministic stable ordering by sorting after injecting scores."}
{"taskId":"BRAIN-PRIORITIZER-URGENT-PATCH","summary":"Implement synthetic urgent remediation entries in prioritizer (ids 0 & 6)","files":["/workspaces/studio/scripts/brain/mission/prioritizer.ts"],"status":"done","createdAt":"2025-08-19T09:55:00.000Z","updatedAt":"2025-08-19T09:53:05.238Z","message":"PATCH INSTRUCTIONS:\nFile: scripts/brain/mission/prioritizer.ts\nGoal: Inject urgent remediation enhancements for ts and lint errors BEFORE computing ordering.\n1. Above prioritizeEnhancements or at top, add doc comment explaining synthetic IDs 0 (urgent TS) and 6 (urgent lint).\n2. Inside prioritizeEnhancements after computing tsErrors/lintErrors etc and BEFORE defining ordering, after scores object and adjustments, insert logic:\n   if (tsErrors > 0) {\n     scores[0] = { score: 100 + tsErrors, title: 'Urgent: Resolve TypeScript errors', reason: `Compilation blockers impede progress (tsErrors=${tsErrors}).` };\n   }\n   if (lintErrors > 0) {\n     scores[6] = { score: 80 + lintErrors, title: 'Resolve ESLint errors', reason: `Lint errors reduce code health (lintErrors=${lintErrors}).` };\n   }\n3. Ensure ordering includes ids 0 and 6 if present (current ordering logic already maps Object.entries(scores)... so just ensure numeric keys allowed).\n4. Maintain existing memory record logic unchanged.\n5. Run typecheck + lint after patch.\nNo other files. Keep diff minimal."}
